This paper deals with NLP tasks and specifically focuses on compressing LSTM networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves matrix factorization algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization tasks, leading to the possibility of it being categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves exploring the effectiveness of the proposed approach on different NLP tasks, which could lead to it being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of biLSTM layers in ELMo, which could lead to it being categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as biLSTMs are commonly used in image processing tasks. Finally, the paper involves compressing LSTMs, which are a type of recurrent neural network, leading to the possibility of it being categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
